manifest_analysis.title:
Application Data can be Backed up
[android:allowBackup=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: This flag allows anyone to backup your application data via adb. It allows users who have enabled USB debugging to copy application data off of the device.
manifest_analysis.name: Application Data can be Backed up [android:allowBackup=true]

nx.description: The shared object does not have NX bit set. NX bit offer protection against exploitation of memory corruption vulnerabilities by marking memory page as non-executable. Use option --noexecstack or -z noexecstack to mark stack as non executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object does not have a stack canary value added to the stack. Stack canaries are used to detect and prevent exploits from overwriting return address. Use the option -fstack-protector-all to enable stack canaries.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has partial RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In partial RELRO, the non-PLT part of the GOT section is read only but .got.plt is still writeable. Use the option -z,relro,-z,now to enable full RELRO.

nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has full RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In Full RELRO, the entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) is marked as read-only.

rpath.description: The shared object does not have run-time search path or RPATH set.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

fortify.description: The shared object does not have any fortified functions. Fortified functions provides buffer overflow checks against glibc's commons insecure functions like strcpy, gets etc. Use the compiler option -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 to fortify functions.

nx.description: The shared object does not have NX bit set. NX bit offer protection against exploitation of memory corruption vulnerabilities by marking memory page as non-executable. Use option --noexecstack or -z noexecstack to mark stack as non executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object does not have a stack canary value added to the stack. Stack canaries are used to detect and prevent exploits from overwriting return address. Use the option -fstack-protector-all to enable stack canaries.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has partial RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. fortify.description: The shared object does not have any fortified functions. Fortified functions provides buffer overflow checks against glibc's commons insecure functions like strcpy, gets etc. Use the compiler option -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 to fortify functions.

nx.description: The shared object does not have NX bit set. NX bit offer protection against exploitation of memory corruption vulnerabilities by marking memory page as non-executable. Use option --noexecstack or -z noexecstack to mark stack as non executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object does not have a stack canary value added to the stack. Stack canaries are used to detect and prevent exploits from overwriting return address. Use the option -fstack-protector-all to enable stack canaries.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has partial RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. nx.description: The shared object does not have NX bit set. NX bit offer protection against exploitation of memory corruption vulnerabilities by marking memory page as non-executable. Use option --noexecstack or -z noexecstack to mark stack as non executable.

playstore_details.title: B Crypto News: Latest Cryptocurrency News
playstore_details.description:
Following the latest cryptocurrency news has never been this easy with the B Crypto News. In this free news app about Bitcoin, Altcoin, Ethereum, and other digital currencies, you get to browse through wide range of crypto news as well as videos, and not only you have access to the title of the news, you can read the whole article as well. 

So, if you are a professional cryptocurrency traded and have already invested in such digital currencies or you have just started to learn about Bitcoin, Altcoin and other currencies, download B Crypto News for free on your Android device and never miss a single crypto news again.

The best news source to follow cryptocurrency news

B Crypto News, the free cryptocurrency news app, comes with a clean and neat design and the interface is so user-friendly that you will get the whole idea after opening the app for the very first time. The app covers the latest news and videos about mining, the blockchain, and cryptocurrencies that saves you lots of time by showing you everything you need to know about digital currencies in one place.

B Crypto News main features at a glance:

- Clean and neat design with a fresh and intuitive interface
- High-quality graphics
- Read the latest cryptocurrency news
- Watch videos about digital currencies
- Useful for both amateur and professional crypto traders and investors
- Read news in Spanish and English languages
- Free to use

So, download B Crypto News for free on your Android device and read the last 50 and most important Cryptocurrency news from @Altcoin Daily! Don’t forget to check out the crypto videos as well.

Stay tuned and let us know about any bugs, questions, feature requests or any other suggestions.
